  "body": "I've noticed that with the newer version (1.5.0), at least under Windows, the logging happens on stdout. In the previous version (1.4.0) it was on stderr (I was redirecting the stderr to a file, and when installing the new version, nothing was being written).\r\n\r\nQuestion: do you write everything to stdout now, both info, warns and errors, or should I save both stdout AND stderr?",
